The paper focuses on studying movement coordination in human ensembles using a computer-based set-up. The study involves investigating the effects of different visual interaction patterns among players and the structure of interconnections among them. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the use of virtual players and agents in the study suggests that the paper could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The use of mathematical models and analysis of coordination levels also suggests that the paper could belong to the Mathematical Aspects (cs.MA) and Control Theory (cs.CY) sub-categories.
